I think I should create a test that catches specific exceptions, using AssertJ to verify that the right exceptions are thrown when trying to read invalid input. There might also be concerns about metadata requirements with Native Image.\n\n**Analyzing BCEL dependencies**\n\nI'm thinking that the class has symbolic references to an absent BCEL, which might lead to issues during native analysis if the method can’t be parsed properly. If a method is reflectively invokable in a native image, it might become reachable, but missing the org.apache.bcel.classfile.ClassParser could cause a \"ClassNotFoundException.\" I wonder if the existing ClassConstants metadata could contribute to these potential build errors, which makes it essential to check how dependencies are structured.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_07d300c03fefa7ac0169fbf5014dcc8194b98ca6997be035f0\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-_Uf6P3QX7X9cKwFuLRO86L-HXC4Y-eFB_Ref9pkapZRilXKdT7apl_wsP7f4kn799F9rN4WDvLB4sqzLFac3jvLSW7n23e3yaDaU6U1ml1x-yEDNb0s47Y5q_di4G4gTPZaHEbpJh_3TUbnhARMZF_zY1ekdlh3I3COpUsyEzInGiW-WzCpJprVXPSZoGbQMEyoEtovOH0o4YXKqOkTmToSL3k8rBzaAE1PlUzYe16HlahTLaocgGctOsUzTJEqyMrClFAXFvMMV1SXkMIAIzDwG3BhfbgtLs4K-DOdrpa3-qlSTFJnofE4trhXhl6dThLpBP8d2Ttakwm7_gSjV6SLzlP3I6MKVP70G2u9nC3u0RM7jVY_9an6MxyMddOBas5402EYCqR_UIarD57wCqU05tnJHKJk7erfpspKkjdPn-yKtdDPWTPRzu-WrCr8u4TdCMPlmuxgpkeTmbdzYO2CU5D8uJne8zbce0YtpBzVuTrj77VI_6mBTNZF86YxNNseo5dOPYvKWPzAb42JjHw0-zyYNy0_f_CL19C3HhgYG6GjaKIPP7EDs_a3xr2dcfd1b_iuBZkqwoiUHIuaAGfA6Ul5OAbmn4iyR3oL9_zW-ClBHuaVlhUmoxRqhpCyxr7tHqhoCWoo0c9xJvG48ZHGZkLy30co6LyGHLEXK1WGVA6nUkzhN9LZPST6HLjYyv6P0WqdoajOdL9htdjkkc2u3lbdpRtVATpAl93R2tDXQERjZkbquySpl9wB4HnQhlI9met3RMyO4Q1b-W79J4wJTVjL1YljcedSPWwLBC-5Jme_nfkPnZBQcJRxuFZK4hF6ca4jbnfCLL0T4X7F4pA7TE29lE6fNlIcTeBKoeKFs-sOUzUShxhbsXz6hc1B4miwUOU4M2PYokS-MbubWdE24gayUQTSpjeYA17Bm8djIwUwpR6PaiijgUbwTUDlY2VNM0Fu_4-qax2hpExZonomNmcQaf8w5kuH1yf4ozcm9fukNMSTuAPunhTPxSF7ZlKnsqsXkhfB58wlSXWt545r9dQMHyA1K30faGvfCNRB5qI30