wever, using native metadata might include test stubs, which might not be advisable.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class definitions**\\n\\nI’m wondering if I could define nested classes without needing a fully qualified class name (FQCN). Maybe I could use actual class generation, but if the stub parser ignores bytes and returns fields correctly, that might not even be necessary. It’s interesting to think about how I can simplify the structure while still getting everything to work. I guess I'll keep exploring this idea!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating testing approach**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether using a test stub public API instead of BCEL is effective since it only tests integration with the helper. The existing Ant artifact expects the optional BCEL, and stubbing dependencies can be helpful. The task specifies not to broaden the source context beyond examples, though. I might consider if using a Reader can aid in producing valid class bytes, but it seems success is really dependent on the encoding and magic byte requirements, which complicates things.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test implementation**\\n\\nI’m mulling over using Ant's ChainReaderHelper with an empty StringReader to trigger the same behavior. If it’s empty, I’d get a bytes length of zero and encounter a BCEL error. I need to measure dynamic-access coverage with JaCoCo, and if `Method.invoke` throws a `NoClassDef`, line 158 may be considered covered. I think I should create a test that catches specific exceptions, using AssertJ to verify that the right exceptions are thrown when trying to read invalid input. There might also be concerns about metadata requirements with Native Image.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing BCEL dependencies**\\n\\nI'm thinking that the class has symbolic references to an absent BCEL, which might lead to issues during native analysis if the method can’t be parsed properly. If a method is reflectively invokable in a native image, it might become reachable, but missing the org.apache.bcel.classfile.ClassParser could cause a \\\"ClassNotFoundException.\\\" I wonder if the existing ClassConstants metadata could contribute to these potential build errors, which makes it essential to check how dependencies are structured.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ZHxOtzD3EEBgGFvrsBmWO0vh|fc_07d300c03fefa7ac0169fbf51faed48194a53be01886f4274d", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "    testImplementation \"ant:ant-xslp:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'xml-resolver:xml-resolver:1.2'\n", "newText": "    testImplementation \"ant:ant-xslp:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'bcel:bcel:5.1'\n    testImplementation 'xml-resolver:xml-resolver:1.2'\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 506, "output": 2033, "cacheRead": 18432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20971, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778119935828, "responseId": "resp_07d300c03fefa7ac0169fbf500794481948cfd4d19d453875e"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_ZHxOtzD3EEBgGFvrsBmWO0vh|fc_07d300c03fefa7ac0169fbf51faed48194a53be01886f4274d", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/build.gradle."}], "details": {"diff": "    ...\n 20     testImplementation \"ant:ant-nodeps:$libraryVersion\"\n 21     testImplementation \"ant:ant-trax:$libraryVersion\"\n 22     testImplementation \"ant:ant-xalan1:$libraryVersion\"\n 23     testImplementation \"ant:ant-xslp:$libraryVersion\"\n+24     testImplementation 'bcel:bcel:5.1'\n 24     testImplementation 'xml-resolver:xml-resolver:1.2'\n 25     jacocoRuntimeAgent \"org.jacoco:org.jacoco.agent:${jacoco.toolVersion}:runtime\"\n 26     testImplementat